    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.20.8-9_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">273 nd Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Crest</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <hi rend="caps">OFFICE OF STATE ADMINISTRATOR
                        <lb/>
                    ILLINOIS
                        <lb/>
                    BANKERS BUILDING
                        <lb/>
                    CHICAGO
                        <lb/>
                    STA</hi>te 2940 
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">TREASURY DEPARTMENT
                        <lb/>
                    <del>DEFENSE</del> <add>WAR</add> SAVINGS STAFF</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 24, 1942</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John G. Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis Post-Dispatch</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>The United States Treasury, in cooperation with the Holy Name Cathedral Book Club, is planning "An Auto-graphing Party for Uncle Sam" on the night of September 9th of this year in the Club Headquarters at Three East Chicago Avenue. All famous authors are being invited in order that the public may secure their autographs by purchasing United States War Bonds and Stamps.</p>
                
                <p>We realize that it would be impossible for you to be present at this event, but we hope to have your help in another way. May we ask you to send us a personally autographed copy of your most famous book which can be auctioned off for a War Bond by a professsional auctioneer?</p>
                
                <p>Thanking you for your cooperation in this matter, which is so important to your Government, I remain,</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed>NORMAN B. COLLINS
                    State Administrator
                    by
                    Mrs Leo P. Cummings
                    Chairman, Catholic Committee
                    War Savings Staff</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>A Man with a Rifle</figDesc>
                    <p>FOR VICTORY
                    BUY
                    UNITED 
                    STATES
                    DEFENSE
                    BONDS
                    AND
                    STAMPS</p>
                </figure>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.20.8-9_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
                <note type="unknown" place="back">Very nice! What book are you sending?</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
